import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='precipitation', kde=True, color='blue', bins=30)
    plt.axvline(data['precipitation'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['precipitation'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of precipitation in Seattle?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Precipitation (mm)")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temp_max', data=data)
    plt.title('How does the maximum temperature vary over time in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Maximum Temperature (°C)')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Max Temperature'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='wind', y='precipitation', hue='weather', palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between wind speed and precipitation in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Weather Condition', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    weather_counts = data['weather'].value_counts()
    sns.barplot(x=weather_counts.index, y=weather_counts.values)
    plt.xlabel('Weather Condition')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the most common weather condition in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
